# ALWAAB ERP — Internationalization (i18n)

The system is fully bilingual (Arabic / English). Every UI change MUST include both languages.

## Vue components

- NEVER hardcode Arabic or English UI strings in `.vue` files
- Import and use: `import { useLocale } from '@/composables/useLocale';`
- Use `const { t, dir, displayName, formatMoney, formatNumber, formatDate } = useLocale();`
- Template strings: `{{ t('module.key') }}` — never literal text for labels, buttons, headings, placeholders (except email examples)
- Layout direction: `:dir="dir"` on page roots (layouts handle this)
- Entity names: `displayName(entity)` — never inline `name_ar`/`name_en` ternaries
- Numbers/dates: `formatMoney()`, `formatNumber()`, `formatDate()` — never `toLocaleString('ar-AE')`
- Table alignment: use `text-start` / `text-end` (logical), not `text-right`/`text-left`
- Confirm dialogs: `t('ui.confirm_*')`

## Translation files

- Add keys to BOTH `lang/ar/{module}.php` AND `lang/en/{module}.php`
- Key naming: `module.descriptive_key` (snake_case)
- Modules: `nav`, `layout`, `ui`, `crm`, `hr`, `invoices`, `quotations`, `chat`, `reports`, `dashboard`, `catalog`, `portal`, `profile`, `settings`, `notifications`
- Translations are auto-shared to Vue via Inertia `translations` prop — no extra wiring needed

## Backend flash messages

- Use `__('module.key')` in PHP controllers/services
- Add the key to both ar/en lang files

## Language switcher

- Header switcher posts to `POST /locale` — do not build custom locale logic
- Sidebar position flips automatically via `dir` attribute (RTL = right, LTR = left)
